    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.5.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno, vim 8.2.3441\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nVTE 0.66.0, ncurses 6.3\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nsystem package manager\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:r!seq 300\r\ngg\r\n:vs\r\n<C-f>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nOnly the left window scrolls.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nThe entire screen scrolls and is not redrawn properly.",
    "closed_at": "2021-11-05T02:36:17Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This is similar to https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/10562, which was fixed before, but is broken again after upgrading to ncurses 6.3.\r\n\r\nI bisected this to https://github.com/mirror/ncurses/commit/f6b436c4fb50275df43ea10ba9c744fe195a327d.\r\n\r\nI believe the problem is that `smglp` and `smgrp` are added for xterm, but like `smglr` they're not implemented by VTE. The hack at https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/5ce35abae6427dac7ac2b147bae8f16adcd8ddff/src/nvim/tui/tui.c#L1661-L1665 needs to be extended to unset `unibi_set_left_margin_parm` and `unibi_set_right_margin_parm` as well.",
